ch.iserver.ace.algorithm.test
Class ExecuteVisitor

java.lang.Object
  ch.iserver.ace.algorithm.test.ExecuteVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
NodeVisitor
Direct Known Subclasses:
NWayExecuteVisitor, TwoWayExecuteVisitor
public class ExecuteVisitor
extends Object
implements NodeVisitor

An ExecuteVisitor is a special node visitor implementation that executes a scenario. The ExecuteVistor makes use of a AlgorithmTestFactory to create algorithms, timestamps and documents. ExecuteVisitor should only be used on a sequence of nodes that is correctly ordered (e.g. operations are generated before they are received).

A Scenario contains such an ordered sequence of nodes. Use Scenario.accept(NodeVisitor) to visit this sequence of nodes.
